    {
      "id": "https://newatlas.com/aging/evening-light-aging-eyes/",
      "url": "https://newatlas.com/aging/evening-light-aging-eyes/",
      "title": "Bright evening light tied to macular degeneration, glaucoma, and cataracts",
      "content_html": "<p><img alt=\"Close up of a person's eye\" src=\"https://assets.newatlas.com/dims4/default/5559adb/2147483647/strip/true/crop/2000x1500+0+0/resize/1280x960!/format/webp/quality/85/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnewatlas-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F94%2F30%2Fd17fb07d464a84c81ece87331e19%2Fclose-up-eye-bright-light.jpg\" /><p>In a massive study of more than 80,000 adults, scientists have found a link between bright artificial light in the evenings and age-related eye disease. At the extreme, light exposure was associated with a 31% higher risk of age-related macular degeneration (AMD), as well as an 18% and 47% increased risk of cataracts and glaucoma, respectively.</p><p><a href=\"https://newatlas.com/aging/evening-light-aging-eyes/\">Continue Reading</a></p><p><b>Category:</b> <a href=\"https://refractor.io/aging/\">Aging Well</a>, <a href=\"https://refractor.io/health-wellbeing/\">Wellness and Healthy Living</a>, <a href=\"https://refractor.io/medical/\">Body and Mind</a></p><p><b>Tags:</b> <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/eye-diseases/\" rel=\"tag\">Eye diseases</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/light/\" rel=\"tag\">Light</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/eye-injury/\" rel=\"tag\">Eye injury</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/glaucoma/\" rel=\"tag\">Glaucoma</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/macular-degeneration/\" rel=\"tag\">Macular Degeneration</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/age-related/\" rel=\"tag\">Age-Related</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/aging/\" rel=\"tag\">Aging</a>, <a href=\"https://newatlas.com/tag/artificial/\" rel=\"tag\">Artificial</a></p>",
      "date_published": "2026-06-23T01:53:41+00:00",
